Since $A = G$, we have $\frac{M+l}{2} \le \frac{k M + m l}{k+m}$.
Manipulating this inequality: $(M+l)(k+m) \le 2(kM + ml) \iff Mk + Mm + lk + lm \le 2kM + 2ml \iff Mm - ml \le kM - lk \iff m(M-l) \le k(M-l)$.
Since $M > l$, we divide by $M-l$ to get $m \le k$.
