Their arithmetic mean is $A = (m + M) / 2$.
By the property, $A$ is the geometric mean of some subset $S$.
Since $m < A < M$, $S$ must contain values greater than $A$ (which must be $M$ as $M$ is the only value $> m$) and values less than $A$ (which must be $\le m$).
Let $S$ contain $p$ copies of $M$ and $q$ values $y_1, \dots, y_q \le m$.
